               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1300">S. XIV</origDate>
                     <origPlace>script probably of <country key="place_1000070">French</country> appearance.</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Perhaps the copy bequeathed by <persName key="person_96800842" role="fmo">Simon Bredon</persName> (so treated by Powicke, pp. 140–1), in any case at the College by <hi rend="italic">c</hi>. 1500. </provenance>
                  <provenance>At the foot of f. 1, against the gutter, are three words, the second and third ‘Galf fl’, perhaps a note of payment to the scribe or decorator. </provenance>
                  <provenance>At the head of f. 1 are ‘Gilbertus’ and the James no. ‘83’, s. xvii in. </provenance>
                  <provenance notAfter="1700" notBefore="1600">Inside the front board is a sheet of paper with titles, s. xvii, and ‘P. 2. 9. Art:’, canc. and replaced with ‘N. 3. 9 (CCXXVI)’ in red. ‘9’ is inked on the foredge; the College bookplate.</provenance>
               </history>
